Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Trim the @carrots{3} then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons. Pop the potatoes and carrots onto separate #baking trays{}. Drizzle both with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and sprinkle the @Italian style herbs{1} over both. Toss each to coat and spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast the potatoes on the top shelf and the carrots on the middle shelf until golden and tender, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through. Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest and halve the @lemon{½}.

Put the @plain flour{1} into a large #bowl{}, season with salt and pepper, then mix together. Sandwich each @British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #cutting board{}, then give it a bash with the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2cm thick. Lay your chicken breast in the bowl, then toss to ensure the chicken gets an even coating of flour. Repeat for the other breasts.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once the oil is hot, lay in the chicken. Cook until golden brown and cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, transfer the chicken to a cutting board, cover with #foil{} and rest for a couple of mins.

Pop the (now empty) frying pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of oil. When hot, add the garlic and the @capers{15} to the pan. Fry for ~{1-2%minutes}, then stir in the @water for the sauce{100%ml} and @chicken stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, then simmer until reduced by half, ~{1-2%minutes}. Vigorously stir in the @unsalted butter{30%g} until melted, then remove from the heat. Add a squeeze of lemon juice and stir together.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if the liquid has evaporated too much.

When everything is ready, stir the lemon zest through the roasted potatoes. Slice the chicken widthways into 5 pieces and serve on plates with the potatoes and carrots alongside. Spoon over the sauce to finish. Enjoy!